        </a>
        <a href="/resources/fcra-explained" style="padding: 24px; border-right: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);">
          <span class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 8px;">// related</span>
          <h4 style="margin-bottom: 6px;">FCRA Explained</h4>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.7;">Fair Credit Reporting Act</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/resources/ftc-consumer-protections" style="padding: 24px; border-right: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);">
          <span class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 8px;">// related</span>
          <h4 style="margin-bottom: 6px;">FTC Consumer Protections</h4>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.7;">Broader FTC consumer protection overview</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/resources/consumer-laws-summary" style="padding: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);">
          <span class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 8px;">// related</span>
          <h4 style="margin-bottom: 6px;">Consumer Laws Summary</h4>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.7;">Quick overview of all consumer protection laws</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="mono" style="margin-top: 24px; font-size: 12px; opacity: 0.5;">
        This page is for educational purposes only and is not legal advice. The FDCPA is codified at 15 U.S.C. §§ 1692–1692p. Enforcement is shared by the FTC, CFPB, and other federal agencies. State laws may provide additional protections.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

